  "What is the definition of 'Two-way table (contingency table)'?": "",
  "\"Two-way table (contingency table)\" means: A table displaying counts for every combination of two categorical variables, with row and column totals (margins). The other options describe different concepts.": "",
  "What is the definition of 'Marginal distribution'?": "",
  "\"Marginal distribution\" means: The distribution of one categorical variable alone, found in the row or column totals of a two-way table. The other options describe different concepts.": "",
  "What is the definition of 'Joint distribution'?": "",
  "\"Joint distribution\" means: The distribution of counts for every combination of categories in a two-way table, expressed as proportions of the grand total. The other options describe different concepts.": "",
  "What is the definition of 'Conditional distribution'?": "",
  "\"Conditional distribution\" means: The distribution of one variable given a specific value of another; found by dividing cell counts by the appropriate row or column total. The other options describe different concepts.": "",
  "What is the definition of 'Simpson's Paradox'?": "",
  "\"Simpson's Paradox\" means: A phenomenon where an association between two variables reverses direction when data are combined across a lurking variable. The other options describe different concepts.": "",
  "Which of the following statements about Categorical Data Analysis is accurate?": "",
  "If the population has mean μ and standard deviation σ, then the sampling distribution of x̄ has mean μx̄ = μ and standard deviation σx̄ = σ/√n (the standard error).": "",
  "Categorical Data Analysis examines the distribution and relationships of categorical variables using frequency tables, relative frequency tables, and bar charts.": "",
  "Measures of center include the mean (arithmetic average sensitive to outliers), the median (resistant middle value), and the mode.": "",
  "Transformations and Power Functions address non-linear relationships by applying mathematical transformations (logarithmic, power, exponential) to achieve linearity.": "",
  "The correct statement describes Categorical Data Analysis as covered in this lesson.": "",
  "Which statement correctly describes an aspect of Categorical Data Analysis?": "",
  "The calculation is identical to the independence test: χ² = Σ(O-E)²/E with df = (r-1)(c-1) and E = (row total × column total)/grand total.": "",
  "Standardization and Z-Scores transform raw data values into a common scale by expressing each observation as the number of standard deviations it falls above or below the mean: z = (x - μ)/σ.": "",
  "Two-way tables (contingency tables) organize counts for two categorical variables and allow calculation of marginal, joint, and conditional distributions.": "",
  "Model comparison using r² and residual plots helps determine which model (linear, exponential, power) best fits the data.": "",
